    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="1059"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1059">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.931/11–646</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 8, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1019.…</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Reurtel 1818 Nov 6 Dept would expect Chinese Govt to waive any taxes fees etc on
                    all property acquisitions and improvements under surplus property agreement on
                    simple basis reciprocity. No transfer taxes or fees charged in US other than
                    recording stamp fee amounting to only few dollars. In negotiations for
                    acquisition full amount transfer taxes fees etc should be credited to US Govt
                    after price property established. Please negotiate carefully on this basis since
                    Dept rather than owners should benefit under this type waiver.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
